gameRecap.title: Game Recap: 76ers 112, Kings 93
gameRecap.excerpt: The 76ers defeated the Kings, 112-93. Tobias Harris puts up 30+ points in back-to-back games for the first time in his career as he notched a season-high 37 points, along with seven rebounds and three assists for the 76ers, while Tyrese Maxey added 21 points and four assists in the victory. De’Aaron Fox tallied 21 points, five rebounds and four assists for the Kings in the losing effort. The 76ers snap a 3-game losing streak as they improve to 24-13 on the season, while the Kings fall to 23-15.
